System Context: We are performing a critical architecture upgrade on the client-side Fabric mod "am-ai mod" (package: com.itdragclick.client.ai) for Minecraft version 26.2.

Our recent runtime logs show severe bugs: the bot hardcodes harvest limits to 16/20 blocks even when asked for a stack, drops collected items at its feet instead of placing them in target chests, hallucinates incorrect item names like "log_acacia", and lacks advanced recursive tool crafting awareness.

Please implement the following modules, command layers, and logic fixes across the codebase. Ensure all operations interacting with the physical world or input states run safely on the main Render/Game thread.

